# JA4proxy-testing — 18-B CVE allowlist
#
# Entries here are CVEs explicitly accepted for a bounded window. Each
# CVE below MUST be preceded by an `# expires: YYYY-MM-DD` comment.
# scripts/ci/check_image_scan.py fails if any entry is expired —
# forcing a decision to fix, re-justify with a new expiry, or remove.
#
# Severity response times (from PHASE_18 acceptance matrix):
#   CRITICAL → decision within 7 days, fix within 30
#   HIGH     → decision within 30 days, fix within 90
#
# Only CRITICAL is a hard merge gate today; HIGH is informational
# until chunk 18-B-2 tightens the gate. That's why the current
# entries are all CRITICAL.

# CVE-2023-24540 (CRITICAL) — Go html/template JS template-literal
# injection in redis:7-alpine. The image pins Go 1.18.2 via its
# upstream base and has not refreshed in ~2 years. Redis itself is
# not a Go html/template user — the vulnerable package is embedded
# in the base image via tools we don't invoke — so impact on this
# deployment is very low. Mitigation: move to redis:7.4-alpine or
# redis:8-alpine once the pin + digest churn is budgeted. Decision
# by expiry.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2023-24540

# CVE-2025-68121 (CRITICAL) — Go crypto/tls certificate validation
# flaw in prom/blackbox-exporter:latest (Go 1.25.5 stdlib in the
# shipped binary). Fixed in Go 1.24.13 / 1.25.7. Blackbox probes
# known internal/external targets over HTTPS from the monitoring
# network; an attacker would need MITM position on the probe path
# to exploit — exposure is bounded but non-zero. Awaiting upstream
# blackbox-exporter image refresh against a fixed Go.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2025-68121
